Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: After those long, treacherous 4 years of sleepless nights, countless projects, and winging all those exams at Purduck University, I've finally made it. My dream job: A mechanical engineer at the one and only Nestla.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: The lobby looks exactly like the pictures too! I'm supposed to meet Elon Duck here to start my first day... but where is he?

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Hello! Sorry to keep you waiting. Are you-

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Elon Duck! Sir! It is a pleasure to finally meet... you... Where is the iconic monocle?

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Haha, I'm sorry to say the boss isn't in the office today. My name is Eggwin. I'll be helping you on your first day here.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I'm assuming you're the new employee then. Main Duck, right?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Quack! That's me!

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Perfect, I already have your first assignment.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: An assignment already? Will I be working on the flying cars I've been hearing so much on the webbed?

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Heh, you're getting your beak in the clouds before even flapping your wings yet. Though with a resume like yours, I'm sure you'll be working in the manufacturing room in no time!

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I was going to suggest your first assignment to be introducing yourself to everyone else in the office. You'll be working with many ducks here on a variety of projects, so I recommend getting to know them as soon as you can.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: That means... I can introduce myself to Duckette! She should be here. She updated her PeepedIn that she was also working here after graduation.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Yes, sir! I look forward to meeting everyone.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Good luck! Here is a list of ducks I would like you to meet. We have quite a few... interesting ducks here, if you catch my drift. So don't let them weird you out.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I'll be here if you either have questions or have finished your first assignment.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Do you have a question?

Name: None
Dialogue: Where can I find Duckette?

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Duckette should be in the office room at her desk. She's almost always on the computer.

Name: None
Dialogue: Where can I find Donald?

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Donald? I wouldn't be surprised if he's slacking in the breakroom. Maybe try checking there?

Name: None
Dialogue: Where can I find Quackson?

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Quackson? I rarely see that duck. I wonder where he could be hiding.

Name: None
Dialogue: I have no questions.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Ok! Be sure to report back once you talk to everyone!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: It's her! It's actually Duckette!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: The ONLY other reason why I picked this job. I can't waste my chances.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hello Duckette! What are the odds that we both got a job at Nestla after graduation?

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Uhh, and you are?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: STRIKE ONE!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Don't you remember me? I'm Main Duck. We both went to Purduck University and studied mechanical engineering.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Hmm, are you sure? I don't recall.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: STRIKE 2!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: We were in that ME 365 together last year.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Oh... maybe.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: AND STRIKE 3! SHE OFFICIALLY DOES NOT REMEMBER ME!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: H-Heh, well, I'm excited to be working with you. I hope we're on the same project!

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Uh, ok! It was nice to meet you.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Oh! Did you need anything?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I need your number, but my beak feels like it's glued shut at the moment.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Uh... no, just saying hi.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: You the new duck?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Yup, that's me! My name is Main Duck.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: I would quit if I were you.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: What? Why?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: You're just like everyone else... dreaming of working for the Elon Duck at Nestla. But everyone is disappearing, flying away like flying cars.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Uh, what do you mean that-

Name: Donald
Dialogue: We just hired someone last week. Now they're gone. The duck we hired the week prior is gone too.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: And yesterday I could've sworn I saw blood in the manufacturing room. Are we really making flying cars?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: What is this duck talking about? I should probably just leave.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Uh, I don't know. But it was nice meeting you? I'm just gonna... go now.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Try to stay alive duck.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: That's not ominous at all.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Argh, I really REALLY got to use the restroom. Why are all the open stalls so dirty?!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Let me see if this first stall is open.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: (Knocks on stall door) Hello? Anyone there?

Name: Quackson
Dialogue: What the quack are you doing? Find a different stall.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I can't use the other stalls! Have you seen the sorry state they're in?

Name: Quackson
Dialogue: So? I'm busy.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Wait... is that Angry Ducks?

Name: Quackson
Dialogue: No.

Name: Quackson
Dialogue: (Flushes toilet).

Name: Quackson
Dialogue: Stall is taken!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: ...I know.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Main Duck, could you ask Duckette for the latest reports? I'll need to review and submit them to Elon Duck by the end of the day.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Quack! You got it!

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Oh, hello there! Can I help you with something?

Name: None
Dialogue: I need something from you.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: What do you need from me?

Name: None
Dialogue: You look impeckable today.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Eggscuse me?

Name: None
Dialogue: Can I help you with something?

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Eggscuse me?

Name: None
Dialogue: Wanna go out?

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Eggscuse me?

Name: None
Dialogue: I need a mechanical part from you.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Umm, what? I don't have that.

Name: None
Dialogue: I need your number.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Umm, what? I don't have that.

Name: None
Dialogue: I need the report.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Oh right, the report that's due today! I have it right here.

Name: None
Dialogue: I need some quack.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Umm, what? I don't have that.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Thanks for the report! I'll get it to Elon Duck right away!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Wow, it's already nighttime! My first day flew by fast.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Everyone's already gone too, even Duckette. Might as well pack up then and get ready to...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: WAIT! Everyone is gone! That means... I have the whole office to myself! I've always wanted to explore the Nestla Office at night.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I can get all the drinks I want from the vending machine, I can finally use the quacking bathroom, and I can take a peep at Duckette's desk. And there's no one here to stop me!

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: Please leave.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: AHH! Where did you come from?

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: Our closing time is 7:00pm. Please leave so I can clean.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Uhh well, can you make one exception? Pretty please? Just give me five minutes?

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: No. Leave or else I'll have to kick you out.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Looks like they're not changing their mind anytime soon. I guess they're pretty strict with their closing hours.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Fineee, have a good night.

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: Goodnight. I encourage you to remember our closing hours next time.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I finished my first assignment!

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: That's egg-cellent! After all, you'll be working with them here at Nestla, so it's best to make those connections now!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Connections... Oh flapping quack, Duckette didn't even remember me! That's not even close to a connection!

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: And you're in luck, I already have your next assignment!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: What if I'm stuck working with an egg-centric like Donald? He gave me the creeps. My feathers stood on end from the weird nonsense he was squawking.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Let me check my duckument here. Hmm, seems like you specialized in mechanical engineering at Purduck University, so you'll probably be suited for CADs.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hmm, I have to find a way to work with Duckette! If we work together, there's no way she could forget a duck like me: hardworking, smart,...

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I'll also need the latest report from Duckette to submit to Elon Duck... something about the new model G.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: With no other duck available, could I trouble you with deliveries too?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I'll be working with Duckette?

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Uhh, were you even listening to me?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Heh... sorry.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I get it. It's your first day, and you're not the first duck to flap out about working at Nestla. But it's important to finish these tasks on time.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Your tasks today should be pretty simple. We need a finished CAD and some deliveries sent out by the end of the day.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Yes, sir! I'll get straight to work.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Duckette here I come to save the day!

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Your task today is to finish a CAD and retrieve the latest report from Duckette.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Quack! You got it.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Another new day, another chance to win Duckette over.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Our first conversation was... wobbly, at best, but this time will be better. I'm sure of it!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh, there she is now! Aww, look at her already typing away. She never was the one to fowl up her responsibilities.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Good morning Duckette, I hope you are having a ducky-tastic day!

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: ...Thanks, whoever you are.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: WHAT?! How could she have NOT liked that? It took me the whole ride here to figure out the best way to greet her.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: She didn't even look at me. Is she actually working or-

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: SQUAWK! Or maybe she's talking to someone!

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Um, can I help you? You've been staring for quite a bit.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: O-Oh, I was just wondering what you're working on today. I have another CAD I need to finish up.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: I'm just responding to emails right now, nothing fancy.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Good luck with the CADs.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hmm, "just" emails? We'll see about that.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I'll be sure to impress Duckette by quacktively tackling my tasks.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Oh, excuse me, intern! If you're on your way to the manufacturing room, can you ask Eggwin for the latest quality test results on the flying cars? I'd really appreciate it.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Quack! You got it!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Duckette needs me! But... I'm not an intern, I'm a junior mechanical engineer here. Just you wait Duckette, I'll prove it to you!

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Ah, Main Duck! It's you! How can I help you today?

Name: None
Dialogue: I need my paycheck.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Huh? Is that really what you came here for?

Name: None
Dialogue: I need my lunch break.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Huh? Is that really what you came here for?

Name: None
Dialogue: I need the latest flying car.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Huh? Is that really what you came here for?

Name: None
Dialogue: I need the test results from you.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Oh, this is for Duckette isn't it? Which test results does she need?

Name: None
Dialogue: Quality of employee's work output.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I'm sorry, I don't have those test results.

Name: None
Dialogue: Quality of the flying cars.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: You're in luck, I just finished collecting those results! Here you go.

Name: None
Dialogue: Quality of Eggwin's pristine feathers.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I'm sorry, I don't have those test results.

Name: None
Dialogue: Quality of the machines.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I'm sorry, I don't have those test results.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: I see you got the test results! Thank you!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: And the damsel in distress was saved... thanks to the duck knight in shining feathers!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Now, what drink would Duckette like?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Should I pick this one?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I'll pick this one then. I hope Duckette likes it!

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Right Drink (Peepsi)
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hello Duckette! This is for you.

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Right Drink (Peepsi)
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Oh? Is that Peepsi?

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Right Drink (Peepsi)
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Yes! Do you... not like Peepsi?

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Right Drink (Peepsi)
Name: Duckette

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Right Drink (Peepsi)
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Ah, I can't read that face! What is swimming in her thoughts right now?

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Right Drink (Peepsi)
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: I'm surprised you didn't get me Quack-a-Cola. I always preferred Peepsi.

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Right Drink (Peepsi)
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Thank you. Main Duck, right?

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Right Drink (Peepsi)
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: SHE KNOWS MY NAME!

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Right Drink (Peepsi)
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: That's one affection point! There's still a waddle of hope for me.

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Wrong Drink for Duckette
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hello Duckette! This is for you.

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Wrong Drink for Duckette
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Thanks intern, just leave it on my desk.

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Wrong Drink for Duckette
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: She barely looked at the drink!

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Wrong Drink for Duckette
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh Duckette, when will I ever be more than an intern to you?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Finally, all the ducks are gone.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I didn't have much luck catching Duckette's attention today, so my only beakon of hope is to see who she was emailing in the morning.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Desperate times call for desperate measures! Time to find Duckette's cubicle.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Quack! I was praying she would forget to sign out. I need to find out what her password is.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I'm in! Time to open her emails...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Looks like there is an email from Elon Duck asking for the latest reports, so that's why she asked for my help.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: ...And there's an email from a Manfred? Who is that? I've never seen them in the office.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: IS SHE ALREADY IN LOVE WITH SOMEONE ELSE?!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: No, no, it can't be! Nestla is huge! I probably haven't met everyone yet. Duckette is one popular duck, after all.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Let's just open this email up just in case...

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: (Footsteps echo in the distance)

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Quack, it's the Janitor! It must be closing hours now!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I already got in trouble yesterday, no need to keep that streak.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I'll leave for the day.

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Sybill
Dialogue: Have you heard? He's coming today!

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Billy
Dialogue: No quacking way, are you pulling my feathers?

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Sybill
Dialogue: No, it's true! He's finally going to show up in the office!

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Fluffy
Dialogue: Oh my duck, I should ask for his signature! I bet all the ducks at home will swoon and drown once they see proof that I get the honor of working for him.

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Billy
Dialogue: Y-You want that?!

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Huh, what is going on? Why is everyone in the lobby?

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh, there's Eggwin in the crowd too! I should ask him what's going on.

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Now, now, I understand the excitement, but as your superior I think we should all return to our office and... Main Duck, you're here!

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Morning Eggwin, what's going on here?

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Oh, you must've overheard them, huh? The ducks have been quacking nonstop after hearing a rumor that Elon Duck will be coming into the office today.

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Really? That's amazing!

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I can finally meet the one and only Elon Duck, pristine feathers and all!

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Ugh, not you too. Again, it's only a rumor.

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: *Whispers* But, between you and me, it's true. Elon Duck is holding a meeting later today, and new employees like you are expected to come.

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Me? I-I'm quite honored that Elon Duck wants me but... What is this meeting about?

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I have no clue. He was pretty vague in his email, but I'm confident that it must be about Nestla's thriving future.

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Elon Duck is actually coming to the office!

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I better leave a good first impression for my boss! Maybe I can buy him a drink before the meeting?

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Don't forget, we'll be having a meeting with Elon Duck today in his office.

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: How can I forget about that? Every duck in this office is quacking about him.

Scene: Elon Duck is in the Office
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I should find a way to leave a good first impression on Elon Duck! Maybe I can get his favorite drink from the vending machine?

Scene: Selecting a Drink for Elon Duck
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Now, what drink would Elon Duck like?

Scene: Drink Choice Confirmation for Elon Duck
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Should I pick this one?

Scene: Drink Choice Selected for Elon Duck
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I'll pick this one then. I hope Elon Duck likes it!

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Right Drink (Energy Gooster)
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Here sir! I bought you a drink from the vending machine before the meeting.

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Right Drink (Energy Gooster)
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Oh? Is that Energy Gooster? That's my favorite drink from our vending machine! I practically live off of these.

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Right Drink (Energy Gooster)
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Heh, y-yeah! It's my favorite too.

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Right Drink (Energy Gooster)
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Why thank you for going out of your way to get me a drink, Main Duck. I'm ducklighted that there is another Energy Gooster fan out there!

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Right Drink (Energy Gooster)
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: You're welcome, sir!

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Right Drink (Energy Gooster)
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: YES! He likes it! That's sure to give me some bonus points. Maybe he'll even write me a recommendation on PeepedIn.

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Wrong Drink for Elon Duck
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Here sir! I bought you a drink from the vending machine before the meeting.

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Wrong Drink for Elon Duck
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Oh? What's this?

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Wrong Drink for Elon Duck
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Ah, I appreciate the gesture, intern, but I'm afraid this isn't my cup of tea. You can have it. I must prepare for the meeting.

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Wrong Drink for Elon Duck
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh, ok...

Scene: If Main Duck Chose Wrong Drink for Elon Duck
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: HE THINKS I'M AN INTERN?! That's just fowl. Maybe I'll have better luck nest time.

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Thank you, my fellow ducks, for meeting with me today. I understand here at Nestla that each and every one of you have a tightly packed schedule, so I will make sure this meeting is as short as possible.

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Firstly, I would like to personally extend my warm welcome to our new employees here at Nestla! My name is none other than Elon Duck, and as you might know, I am this company's founder. I apologize for the rather late introducktions.

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Introducktions aside, I believe it is necessary to reiterate the importance of collaboration and teamwork here at Nestla. It takes a team of talented ducks like yourselves to continue the improvement of Nestla's famous flying cars.

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Without such a team that is dedicated to innovation and beak-tiful technological progress for all duck-kind, Nestla would cease to exist!

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: And it is because of this importance of teamwork that I am announcing my plan to hire new recruits in the upcoming days. I hope each and every one of you can extend a lending wing to our new recruits, just like how our dear Eggwin helped Main Duck on their first day.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Wow, Nestla really is big if Elon Duck is thinking about hiring more employees. I'm going to quickly rise up at Nestla in no time!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: *Mutters* Of course Elon Duck is hiring more recruits. It's not like this is the first time.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Huh, Donald doesn't seem all that pleased about Elon Duck's announcement.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Now that I think about it, he was complaining about the constant hiring of ducks when we first met too. But isn't hiring more ducks a good thing?

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: With my announcement out of the way, the meeting is now over. Thank you everyone for attending and remember to look out for future emails regarding upcoming meetings and tasks. Everyone is dismissed.

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: That is the end of today's meeting. Thank you everyone for taking the time out of your busy schedules.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Hey, you're not busy, right? Can you help me find my notes?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Notes? What notes?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: They're my notes for my speech! My speech will finally make a splash on the unassuming pond of Nestla, showing what's hidden under the water. Once the other ducks listen to me, they will finally have their ducks in a row.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I am so lost right now.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Look, I'm a little busy right now and-

Name: Donald
Dialogue: I looked at your schedule, you only have one task later in the day. You have time.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: What a quacking creep.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Fine, I'll help you find your notes.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: There it is! I can't believe that egg-centric left his notes here in Elon Duck's office.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Wait... is that Elon Duck? Reading the notes?!

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Ah, if it isn't Main Duck. Did you forget something?

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round1_Option1
Name: None
Dialogue: I need my paycheck.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round1_Response1
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Hmm? Come again?

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round1_Option2
Name: None
Dialogue: I need your autograph.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round1_Response2
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Hmm? Come again?

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round1_Option3
Name: None
Dialogue: I need those notes.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round1_Response3
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Notes? You mean these? Are these yours?

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round1_Option4
Name: None
Dialogue: I need a speech.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round1_Response4
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Hmm? Come again?

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Option1
Name: None
Dialogue: Yes, those are mine.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Response1
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Now, now, Main Duck. It's not good to lie.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Option2
Name: None
Dialogue: No, those are Donald's.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Response2
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: I assumed they were his. And it looks like he asked you to retrieve it for him.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Response2
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: I must say, it was quite an amusing read.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Response2
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Heh, you think? He didn't tell me what the notes were about.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Response2
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: It's the same old horror story of ducks going missing here at Nestla. Ha, what a dramatic duck!

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Response2
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: I mean, come on. Kidnapping? Killings? I think Donald should spend that talent writing books, not spreading propa-gander.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Response2
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Do you want to know why ducks are supposedly "going missing?"

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Response2
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Uh, yes sir! I would like to know.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Response2
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Well little duckling, it's because so many ducks are quitting! Isn't that a shame?

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Response2
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Nestla is a competitive company of innovation, and we are always looking for ducks that fit the bill, ducks that can solve the next generation of challenges.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Response2
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Working here is not for the faint of heart, and many have quit before finishing their first week here, complaining about the overwhelming workload.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Response2
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: But I have a waddle of hope for ducks like you Main Duck. I look forward to seeing what you bring here to Nestla.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Response2
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Wow, Elon Duck actually has his wing around me!

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Response2
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Now, I've kept you up long enough. You best return these to Donald. I'll be in my office if you need anything.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Option3
Name: None
Dialogue: No, those are Duckette's.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Response3
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Now, now, Main Duck. It's not good to lie.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Option4
Name: None
Dialogue: No, those are Eggwin's.

Scene: Ask Elon Duck for Retrieval Item_Round2_Response4
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Now, now, Main Duck. It's not good to lie.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: You found my notes!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Yup, they were in Elon Duck's office.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I probably shouldn't tell him about my encounter with Elon Duck.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Hmm, I must have accidentally left them after our meeting.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: But now with my notes, I can finally give my speech! You best attend Main Duck.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: ...I don't think I even have a choice.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Fellow ducks! Your attention please!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Ahem! Your attention!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: No one gives a quack. Even Duckette is scrolling on her phone.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: *Sigh* Donald, is there a problem with the current production of Nestla's Model G?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: The better question is whether there is a problem with Nestla itself.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Donald, if this is another one of your crazy theories, I suggest-

Name: Donald
Dialogue: A theory that has just been proven! And I have the notes all here as proof, which I diligently wrote during our meeting!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Ducks! All of you are aware that Elon Duck has asked a few of us, including me, to attend a meeting. But I'm sure most of you are pondering about what the meeting was even about.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: No, it was not about the new Model G, but about his plan to recruit new ducks. And it does not take a ducktective to note how he has been consistently hiring more and more ducks. But why?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Well, it is because our fellow ducks keep disappearing one by one! Have you ever wondered what happened to Webster? Quackie? Ducktilda?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: One day, they were working right alongside us. The next day... Poof. Gone. Not even a feather remained.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: They likely quit and didn't bother sending in their resignation.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Oh, but that's what they want you to think. But how do you eggs-plain how sudden it was? Did the missing ducks simply leave or was there fowl play involved?

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Their desks were empty the next day. They likely packed their things and moved on with their lives.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Again, the evidence was merely thrown away to cover up the true reason behind the disappearances...

Name: Donald
Dialogue: ...Our fellow ducks were duck-napped! Killed! Why else would they disappear so suddenly without a word?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: And who is behind this? Our boss! Elon Duck! He's not hiring ducks for the betterment of the company but to cover up the disappearances. He's up to something... and after several years of working here I can say that I am closer to the truth!

Name: Sybill
Dialogue: Isn't that a stretch?

Name: Fluffy
Dialogue: That's, like, one hundred percent NOT proven.

Name: Billy
Dialogue: Elon Duck wouldn't do that. Look at how many ducks and other birds he has helped with his amazing inventions! Without my Nestla Model D, I'd be a sitting duck. Literally.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Huh, Elon Duck really was right. Donald's speech is practically duckspeak while Eggwin's rebuttals make more sense.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: But-

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Alright everyone, now that that's out of the way, please return to work.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I suggest you do that too, Donald.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: *Mutters* Don't say I didn't warn you.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: No one ever quacking listens.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Just you wait. One day, everyone will know that I was right.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Hello Main Duck. Are you ready for your next task?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Quack! I'm ready!

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Great, you'll be tasked with training the autopilot AI for the new Model G Flying Car. We've already uploaded the proper models and data into VR.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: All you have to do is drive and avoid the obstacles.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: If you have no further quacktions, I'll start up the simulation now.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I have no quacktions. I can't wait to finally test something for the new Model G!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: This is my chance at getting a test drive in before it hits the market!

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Then the simulation starts in 3...2...1.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Woah, that was a quacking awesome ride! I can't wait to purchase one for myself once it's out!

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: ...You're gonna have to wait a little longer, Main Duck. You've only tested one of the many systems, and it was only in a simulation.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hey, no need to ruffle my feathers like that.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I was simply bringing you back to the ground.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I've recorded the results from the prototype training task in this report. Can you give it to Duckette?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Quack! Of course I can!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Wow, 2 days in a row I get to report to Duckette! I'm one lucky duck!

Scene: Hand Nestla Prototype Testing Results to Duckette
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hello Duckette! I have the report with the new results!

Scene: Hand Nestla Prototype Testing Results to Duckette
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: What results?

Scene: Hand Nestla Prototype Testing Results to Duckette
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Results from the recent simulation run of the new Model G's autopilot AI system.

Scene: Hand Nestla Prototype Testing Results to Duckette
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: And I was the one who got to test it!

Scene: Hand Nestla Prototype Testing Results to Duckette
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Oh, those results. Yes, please put them on my desk, I'll go through them after I finish this email.

Scene: Hand Nestla Prototype Testing Results to Duckette
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Ah, as diligent as ever I see.

Scene: Hand Nestla Prototype Testing Results to Duckette
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: As for me, that should be my last task for the day!

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Impeckable work today everyone! I have just finished going over the latest progress on Model G, and I must say that I am beyond impressed!

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: As thank you for the hard work, everyone can leave early. No need to stay behind to finish last minute work.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Yes! That means I have more time to figure out how I'm gonna win over Duckette.

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Oh, I almost forgot! Can Duckette, Billy, and Fluffy stay behind for a couple of minutes? I would like to discuss the shipment of the new Model G parts that should be coming in a couple of days.

Name: Fluffy
Dialogue: Finally, someone remembered my name!

Name: Sybill
Dialogue: Wait your name is Fluffy?!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: ...The Duck Gods are against me.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But why were those 3 ducks chosen, including Duckette? Each one of them plays a different role on the team, and from what I've seen, they rarely talk to each other.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: And more importantly... WHY WASN'T I PICKED?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hmmm... I mean, I could stay behind again and try to peep in on the conversation. But the Janitor has already caught me once. Can't have him quacking on me to the boss himself.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I know! I'll ask Duckette about the meeting tomorrow.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: A new day, a new opportunity to talk to Duckette!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: *Sigh* I could barely sleep last night. I stayed up pondering on what Duckette and Elon Duck could've quacked about.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But now I can ask her! She should be at her desk-

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Huh? Where's Duckette? She's usually very punctual, even back when we were at Purduck.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: She couldn't be... no, no that would never happen to a duck like her! Every duck in the office agrees that Donald's speech was webbed with his wacky theories yesterday.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I should ask Eggwin if he's seen Duckette today.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Oh, good morning Main Duck. How can I help-

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: HAVEYOUSEENDUCKETTE?!

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Woah, slow down! Can you repeat that?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Sorry. Have you seen Duckette?

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: No, I haven't seen her in the office today. Did something urgent come up?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: What's urgent is that she's not here!

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: It's pretty normal for a duck or two to not be in the office, Main Duck. She's probably taking a sick day.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But she was perfectly fine yesterday. I don't even remember her taking one sick day in college!

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Well, some things happen out of our control. Just you wait, she'll be back tomorrow.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Now, I suggest you return to work. We have a busy day ahead of ourselves.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: There's no way this is a coincidence. First Donald gives his crazy speech and now Duckette has disappeared?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh no, what if Duckette becomes another missing duck in Donald's stories! I'll never have the chance to see her again.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I need to find Duckette, no matter what. I'll be her duck knight in shining feathers if that's what it takes to save her!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But... where do I even start? The only one who might know is...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: ...Donald. He should be in the breakroom.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I suggest you return to work. We have a busy day today.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I'm sure Duckette will return to work tomorrow.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Donald? I have a quacktion for you.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Is it about the missing ducks?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: How did you...?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Nevermind... yes, it's specifically about Duckette. What are, um, the chances that she's disappeared like, you know, in the rumors?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: ...Where did you get the extra 1%?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: The second I came to the office, I immediately knew something was up.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Don't you think it's strange that the same ducks that met with Elon Duck after work: Duckette, Billy, and Fluffy, are not here?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Who were those last two again?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: That doesn't matter. What matters is that another duck also realizes that something is up with this place! I'm not crazy! Oh, this is beyond bill-iant!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I still think you're slightly crazy...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But desperate times call for desperate measures.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Look, I think Duckette missing a day of work doesn't fit the bill at all, especially without any eggs-planation. So, I need to find out where she has gone. Can you help me?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: You've come to the best duck for the job!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: I haven't launched my investigation into the most recent disappearance yet because Eggwin's been on my tail feather today, nagging me about work.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: But if you're willing to be my duck partner in crime, then we can both work together to find some clues around this place. Two ducks are better than one, and we can share what we discover.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: He does make a good point. And besides, Duckette needs me.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Fine, I'll work with you... for Duckette!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Haha, I can already feel that we're closer to solving this disappearance case!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: ...WE HAVEN'T EVEN STARTED YET!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: The first thing we need is evidence.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Evidence?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Of course! No one will believe us if we don't have evidence.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Says the same duck who is known for his crazy conspiracies. Barely any of the ducks paid attention to his speech yesterday.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: The most recent batch of ducks that have gone missing was last night. So, there's got to be evidence lying around here somewhere.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: *Sniffs* Poor Duckette.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Oh, for quacking out loud, smooth your ruffled feathers already. Crying won't save Duckette.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: If you really want to save her, help me search around the offices for clues.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Y-You're right, maybe Duckette left something behind for us!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: There must be something around this place that's connected to the missing ducks.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: I suggest searching around the offices for clues.

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 1
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hey! Have you seen anything suspicious?

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 1
Name: Meggan
Dialogue: Suspicious? Like what?

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 1
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Something related to the missing ducks?

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 1
Name: Meggan
Dialogue: *Sigh* Not you too.

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 1
Name: Meggan
Dialogue: We already have Donald, we don't need a Donald Jr.

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 1
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Well that was quacking rude.

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 1
Name: Meggan
Dialogue: For your information, I haven't seen anything.

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 1
Name: Meggan
Dialogue: Now if you'll eggs-cuse me, I need to return to work.

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 2
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hey! Do you have any information about the ducks that have gone missing?

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 2
Name: Eggric
Dialogue: Ducks have gone missing?

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 2
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: This guy is quacking oblivious.

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 2
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Have you not noticed that the office is emptier than yesterday?

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 2
Name: Eggric
Dialogue: Really? It looks the same to me.

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 2
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Well, did you know that ducks like Duckette haven't shown up at work yet?

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 2
Name: Eggric
Dialogue: Maybe they're taking a sick day?

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 2
Name: Eggric
Dialogue: Or maybe ducks like Duckette just needed a day off.

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 2
Name: Eggric
Dialogue: *Sigh* You know, I could use a day off. My wings are cramping from operating these machines all day.

Scene: Optional - Talk to Ducks about Investigation 2
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: This is going nowhere. I should try looking somewhere else.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Huh, what's this? It looks like a-

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: AHHHH! There's <color=red>blood on this feather!</color>

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Why is there blood on this feather?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: And why is it in front of Quackson's stall?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Either way, from all the ducktective shows I've seen, which is only two, anything with blood is always a piece of evidence.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I should probably ask Quackson about this when I have the chance.

Scene: Quackson Dialogue Day 4 - After Finding Bloody Feather
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Quackson, do you know what this is?

Scene: Quackson Dialogue Day 4 - After Finding Bloody Feather
Name: Quackson
Dialogue: It's a feather that you painted red?

Scene: Quackson Dialogue Day 4 - After Finding Bloody Feather
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: It's blood actually.

Scene: Quackson Dialogue Day 4 - After Finding Bloody Feather
Name: Quackson
Dialogue: Where did you get a bloody feather from?

Scene: Quackson Dialogue Day 4 - After Finding Bloody Feather
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Funny story, it was in front of your stall. Do you know anything about it?

Scene: Quackson Dialogue Day 4 - After Finding Bloody Feather
Name: Quackson
Dialogue: Sorry ducktective, but you're the first duck I've seen today. The feather is not mine, and the feather is not yours.

Scene: Quackson Dialogue Day 4 - After Finding Bloody Feather
Name: Quackson
Dialogue: But the vents have been acting up lately. Who knows, maybe some drunk duck decided to go into the vent, and they got caught in the exhaust fan?

Scene: Quackson Dialogue Day 4 - After Finding Bloody Feather
Name: Quackson
Dialogue: *Whispers* And the bloody feather was all that was left of them.

Scene: Quackson Dialogue Day 4 - After Finding Bloody Feather
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Is this for real or is Quackson pulling my tailfeathers?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Wait, what's this in front of Elon Duck's office?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: No... it can't be!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: It's <color=red>Duckette's beak-tiful necklace</color>! What's it doing here?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Even at Purduck, she was always wearing this necklace. I never saw her take it off once.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Maybe... Maybe this is a sign of a struggle between Duckette and the ducknapper!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Maybe... they yanked her necklace off before-

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: No, I can't finish that thought. She can't be hurt... right?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh Duckette... don't worry, I'll save you!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Looks like no one is at the receptionist's desk today.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I'm sure they won't mind if I take a little peep.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Let's see, there's a picture frame, reminders for meetings and evaluations, a list of tasks...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Wait, there's another duckument underneath all these papers.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: It seems to be a <color=red>record of all the latest deliveries</color>.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: There are some packages that have arrived for the Model G, as well as another supply of Energy Gooster... 10 boxes?! Surely that won't all fit in the vending machine?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But... there's also an <color=red>unnamed package</color> that was picked up today too. And the only description under it is "parts."

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: It's the only unnamed package in the record. It's weird that there's not even a name or who it was sent to.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I should note this down before the receptionist returns.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Donald! I found some evidence!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Oh? What did you find?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I found a <color=red>bloody feather</color> in the bathroom, <color=red>Duckette's necklace</color> in front of Elon Duck's office, and a <color=red>record about an unnamed package</color> picked up from this office this morning.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Wow, quack-tastic job Main Duck! This is the most evidence I've ever stumbled upon in my time at Nestla.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: I would love to talk more about what you found, but we should return to work before we continue our investigation. We don't want the others getting suspicious.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: You're expected to complete another CAD by the end of the day, correct?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Quack, you're right! I'll get right on that!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Hey, before you go, there's one more thing.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Try to stay behind after all the ducks leave. We'll continue where we left off after the offices close.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: You got it! But... what about the Janitor?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Ah, I see you you've already met the Janitor.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: The Janitor only gets angry once it's after 7:00pm. But since most of the ducks leave at 5:00pm, we should have about two hours to investigate.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I hope that's enough time...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Ok! I'll see you tonight then!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Stay on your guard, Main Duck.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Make sure to finish your tasks before Eggwin gets suspicious.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: We don't want him poking his beak where it doesn't belong.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: We'll finish our ducktective work at night.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Ok, time to finish this CAD so no one suspects of me of quacking off.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Let's see what I'm putting together this time!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Done!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But... something seems off about this design.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Maybe it's because my mind is currently in ducktective mode, but would the manufacturing for the new Model G really need something like this?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Either way, I'll save a copy of this design just in case.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Phew, what a day! Being a mechanical engineer AND a ducktective is hard work.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But I can't go home now since Donald and I are staying behind to continue investigating at night.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Barely anyone is left in the office now. I should go find Donald.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Main Duck, can I talk with you for a second?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Uh oh, what does Eggwin want? Play it cool, play it cool.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: S-Sure Eggwin, what's up?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: QUACK! I stuttered.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I noticed you were slacking around with Donald for the majority of the day.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Though you still finished your tasks, I'm worried how this will affect producktion going forward if you continue this behavior.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Shoot, Donald was right. Eggwin is pretty observant. Maybe I should tell him about my worries. It couldn't hurt, right? I mean, Eggwin should be aware of the disappearances.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I was only talking to Donald about what he thinks about the duck disappearance cases. Duckette, Quacksly, and Fluffy are absent today. It can't be a coincidence.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: *Sigh* Main Duck, I must strongly advise you to not believe every rumor you hear, especially out of Donald's beak. Nothing good can come out of falling for Donald's crazy schemes.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: There are many reasonable eggs-planations as to why some ducks are not here today.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: And, from duck to duck, I want you to know just how quack-tastic this company is. I've worked for Nestla for a little over a year now and it's been the best job I've ever had.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: The pay itself is pond-erful. The flying cars we make as well not only help other ducks, but all of bird-kind. Imagine the birds who can't even fly and can benefit from what we do.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: And between you and me, I have unwavering confidence in both our fellow ducks and Elon Duck.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: We're making a splash here at Nestla. So, I have faith in Nestla and Elon Duck. Don't be deterred by mere rumors.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh quack, he gave me a whole speech and everything! He's definitely suspicious.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: He does make a few decent points, but there's still something up with this place and how it connects to the disappearances.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I should just nod along for now.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Of course, Eggwin. I really needed to hear that.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Anytime, Main Duck. If you ever find yourself doubtful again, be sure to come to me.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Now, I gotta get going. Are you leaving too?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Uh, yes! I just left something at my desk, so I'll go grab it before leaving.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Ok, then I'll see you tomorrow Main Duck. Have a good night!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Goodnight!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Finally, he's gone. I gotta be more careful now.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Anyways, Donald's probably wondering where I'm at. I should find him now.

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Donald
Dialogue: There you are! I was beginning to think that you had already forgotten about the investigation.

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Please, how can I forget about everything I just found out today?

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Sorry, I was stopped by Eggwin.

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Donald
Dialogue: Egghead?

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: No, Eggwin.

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Donald
Dialogue: Ah, Elon Duck's pet.

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Pet?

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Donald
Dialogue: Come on, you don't need a conspiracy for that. It's obvious how loyal Eggwin is to Elon Duck.

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Donald
Dialogue: Eggwin is always poking his beak in places he doesn't need to be. And he's always eager to snitch on me to Elon Duck on the tiniest of things.

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Donald
Dialogue: So, let me guess, he's on to us?

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Dang, Donald got it right on the beak.

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Yeah, he tried to tell me to stay loyal to the team and that I shouldn't be worried about the missing ducks.

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Eggwin really believes that there is a simple eggs-planation to the missing ducks.

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But after what I found out today, it's one hundred percent, without a doubt, something we should be worried about.

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Donald
Dialogue: And he's already left the office?

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Yes, I made sure of it. I made up an eggs-cuse that I forgot something at my desk, and he seemed to have bought it.

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Donald
Dialogue: Good, because we can't have Eggwin in the way of our investigation.

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Donald
Dialogue: Now, we can't waste any more time. We're on a time crunch if we want to avoid the Janitor.

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Donald
Dialogue: Based on the evidence you've found, our best bet is to search Elon Duck's office.

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: We're breaking into his office?!

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Donald
Dialogue: He was the last duck with the missing ducks, remember? He's bound to have some sort of information somewhere in there.

Scene: Meet up with Donald at Night
Name: Donald
Dialogue: Let's go.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Welp, I knew it.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: His office is locked.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Not for long. Good thing I always carry this around with me!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: No quacking way, is that a lockpicking kit?!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Why do you have this eggs-actly?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: A word of advice as my partner in this investigation, it's always a good idea to carry around a lockpicking kit in case you need to unlock something!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: My feathers ruffle at what Donald has used that kit for...

Name: Donald
Dialogue: And so, you're in luck, you'll be using it.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Wait...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: WHAAAAAAT?!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: WHY ME?!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: It's a valuable skill to have, Main Duck.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Come on, give it a try. Use this kit to unlock Elon Duck's office.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh for quacking out loud...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Fine, hand it over. I wouldn't get your hopes up though.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I... I DID IT!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: There we go! Great job, Main Duck! Now we can investigate Elon Duck's Office.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: *sigh* I can't find anything over here... Besides evidence of this duck's ego problem.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Look, Elon Duck left his laptop here. Maybe we'll find evidence on here.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Oooh, great idea Main Duck! I knew you were the perfect duck for the job!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Heh, well I have hacked into Duckette's computer before...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Though it's strange that Elon Duck left his phone here. Maybe he was in a hurry?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Let's see here...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Welp, his phone is locked. And I don't know the password.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Hey, don't look at me! Do I look like I know the CEO's password?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Well, I bet my bills and pristine feathers that you have a better idea than me! Clearly Elon Duck himself wouldn't leave his password lying about.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: ...We can always guess the password.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Are you quacking insane? That will take all our duck years! We only have two hours before the Janitor comes, remember?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: All the more reason to start guessing.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: This is quacking stupid.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Nestla. Wrong.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Elon Duck. Wrong.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Duck. Wrong.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Goose?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Goose? Why Goose?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: You know, Duck, Duck, Goose? Goose chases the duck? No duck would ever set goose as their password.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: And the last thing a CEO of a big company wants is for their phone to be hacked. Goose is stronger than any randomly generated password!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: ...I should've guessed something like that would come out of Donald's beak. Personally, I prefer my random passwords.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I'll just give it a try before testing a different password.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Goose... Hey! It actually worked! I'm in!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: There's... a bunch of emails on the screen. Being a CEO must be tough.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But I can't read a quacking thing.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: It looks to be encrypted... which is even more suspicious if you ask me.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: *mutters* Elon Duck... what are you hiding?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: And it's not like I can look through his desk for a password or something, this takes serious coding skills!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Don't worry, because I have another tool just for this!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: How many tools does this duck have?! And why didn't he have one when we were guessing the password?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: This here is what I call a duckryption tool. It'll take all the encrypted text and decrypt it so we can read it!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: A prompt should appear on the screen, and if the program is run successfully, we should be able to find out what Elon Duck is hiding.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Well, here goes nothing!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Yes! It worked! We can read Elon Duck's emails now.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Let's see... looks like most of these emails are between Elon Duck and-

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: THE DUCKBERRY FARM?!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: So that's the secret...

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Move over, let me give it a read.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Hmm... it looks like Nestla has been in kahoots with this duck farm called Duckberry this whole time.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: And his last email reads that "The next shipment of ducks is already being processed. The parts will be prepared and sent for delivery in the next few days."

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Those "parts" aren't what I think they are... right?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Well, I certainly don't think they are the mechanical kind.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: This is definitely related to the case of the missing ducks. In fact, it's a major breakthrough!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But that means... Duckette and the others...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: THEY'RE IN DANGER!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: It's not looking too promising, that's for sure. I'll take a picture of this and copy down this email.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: We'll reconvene tomorrow. Let's head out before the Janitor spots us.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: There you are, Main Duck! What's quacking?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: What do you mean, "What's quacking?!" We just learned that Elon Duck is in kahoots with some duck farm! Duckette could already be a sitting duck!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Shhh, quiet down. Eggwin already seems suspicious of us. We don't need him poking his feathery head in here.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: What, do you have a plan?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Listen, what do you think is the most important evidence we found yesterday?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Besides that fowl email, it has got to be Duckette's broken necklace we found right outside of Elon Duck's office!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Elon Duck probably grabbed her by the neck and ripped the necklace right off!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: ...While I agree Elon Duck is one fowl duck, I was actually talking about the bloody feather we found in the bathroom.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: We know the necklace belongs to Duckette and that led us to breaking into Elon Duck's office. That's when we discovered the email.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: There is also the unnamed package. While I have an idea of what it could possibly be, especially after reading the email, I don't have enough evidence yet.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: So, our best bet is the bloody feather.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Because the bloody feather can lead us to the missing ducks?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Eggs-actly! I did my own ducktective work while you were finishing your tasks yesterday. Did you know that strange noises would usually come from the bathroom?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Isn't that true for every bathroom?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: You know what I mean. There's a faint rattling from above.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: And if you haven't noticed, Quackson is sure to have noticed for being in the bathroom 24/7.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh, I get it! We should talk to Quackson then. Maybe he knows something about the strange sound or the bloody feather.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: We should find that Quackson. He should know something about this bloody feather.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Quackson?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Quackson? I know you're in there. Donald and I just have a few quack-tions for you.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: I'm gonna open the door.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: NO, YOU ARE NOT!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: What? We need to talk to him.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Do you just normally open closed bathroom doors? They're closed for a reason!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: But we have a good reason. Anyways, he's probably just reading his newspaper or playing Angry Ducks behind the newspaper.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: If I were you Quackson I would finish whatever you're doing and-

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Too late! We've given him enough time.

Name: None
Dialogue: Donald breaks open the door, only for them to stumble upon <color=red>Quackson's dead body</color> slumped against the toilet.

Name: None
Dialogue: Blood is splattered across the bathroom tiles and walls, but most of the blood seems to pool out from the numerous stab wounds on Quackson's body with no sign of stopping.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: *Gags* Oh my duck, he's quacking dead!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Well, we have officially stumbled upon our first body.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: FIRST?!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: His wounds are fresh. He was likely just killed this morning.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Either someone knows we would question Quackson or that Quackson knew something he shouldn't know. And I wouldn't be surprised if it was both.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I think I'm going to be sick-

Name: Donald
Dialogue: The toilet is available now.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Too soon.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hey, I just noticed. There's a vent right above Quackson's head.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: You know, the rattling sound did come from above...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: You think it came from the vents?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: I mean, where else could it have come from? It's our only clue.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: I've been in the breakroom this entire time. No one went in or out of the bathroom.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: So, the only way the killer could kill Quackson would be if they traveled using the vents.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: And why are you looking at me like that?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Someone's got to check inside the vent. I'll be on watch duty in case anyone suspects your absence.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Of course, I have to go into the creepy vent. Let's just hope I don't get lost in there.

Name: None
Dialogue: Main Duck takes a deep breath before hopping onto the toilet seat and climbing into the vent.

Name: None
Dialogue: Main Duck notes the stray feathers scattered throughout the vent and uses this trail to waddle their way in the dark.

Name: None
Dialogue: Surprisingly, it's not as dusty as Main Duck expected it to be, which means this vent has either been frequently used for discreetly traveling from place to place...

Name: None
Dialogue: ...or that the Janitor really likes to keep every corner of the place clean.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Finally, freedom at last!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Who would've thought that Donald was right? There really is a secret room in Nest-

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: AHHH! WHAT THE QUACK IS ALL THIS?!

Name: Eggric
Dialogue: Help!!! Don't just stand there, quacking do something!

Name: Peeper
Dialogue: mAmA!!!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: W-What? Huh?

Name: Quacksly
Dialogue: AHHHHHHH!

Name: None
Dialogue: Main Duck helplessly watches as the killing machine in the center of the room slaughters one of the ducks.

Name: None
Dialogue: Cardboard boxes dripping with blood are stacked beside the machine, and scattered feathers are littered across the floor.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: That m-machine, it looks familiar... almost like all the CADs I was assigned to this week!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: We're not making parts for the new Model G... we're making a killing machine for ducks! But why?!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Maybe Duckette is already... No, no, of course not, that can't be! She must be in one of these cages.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I know! I'll try to save as many ducks as I can. Maybe then I'll find Duckette and impress her as the feathered savior.

Name: None
Dialogue: With no time to lose, Main Duck makes it their mission to check every cage in the slaughterhouse in the hopes of finding Duckette alive.

Name: None
Dialogue: Along the way, Main Duck attempts to free the rest of the ducks, but only manages to save a few.

Name: None
Dialogue: Most were already dead or too close to those awaiting gates in the sky.

Name: None
Dialogue: Others had complex locks that even Donald's lockpicking kit couldn't unlock.

Name: None
Dialogue: And so, Main Duck loses track of time in this numb, rhythmic cycle: Check a cage, find no Duckette, try to save the duck, face a corpse instead or a duck awaiting death, pray Duckette isn't next, and move on to the next cage.

Name: None
Dialogue: By the time Main Duck has triple checked every single cage in the slaughterhouse, only a few ducks have been saved and no Duckette.

Name: Eggna
Dialogue: Main Duck, you're, like, our feathered angel!

Name: Quacklyn
Dialogue: We would've been a sitting duck without you!

Name: Billtrix
Dialogue: Thank you for saving us, Main Duck!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Was I too late? Duckette is nowhere to be found!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: What if... the killing machine already got her?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: No, she must still be alive. Maybe there's another slaughterhouse?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But... it's already getting late. I can't risk getting caught.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I should get everyone out of here first and then report to Donald.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: It's getting late. Here, get yourselves in a row and follow me! I'll get us all out of here!

Name: None
Dialogue: Main Duck then leads the surviving ducks back through the vents.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Ok, this should take me back to the bathroom.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I'll look for Donald first and make sure the office is clear before these ducks can return home.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: *Whispers* Ok ducks, stay here while I make sure the coast is clear.

Name: Ducks
Dialogue: *Whispers* Quack!

Name: None
Dialogue: Main Duck exits the vents and finds themselves in Quackson's stall again with Quackson's rotting body.

Name: None
Dialogue: Swallowing the bile rising in their throat, Main Duck opens the stall door.

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: Please leave.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: AHHH ITS QUACKSON'S KILLER!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: The Janitor? Where did you come from?

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: We are reaching closing hours. Most ducks have left the office. Please leave so I can clean.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Uhh well, can you make one exception? I'm kinda busy with-

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Wait a quacking second, what are you doing here?

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: My job is to clean. Please leave or else I will have to kick you out.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Strange. The Janitor hasn't even reacted to Quackson's dead body.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: And isn't this the entrance to the slaughterhouse? The Janitor was right outside this stall door, almost as if...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Were you about to... go into the vents to go to the slaughterhouse? Do you have any idea what is even happening to our kind in there?

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: <color=red>Error: They are not my kind.</color>

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: ...What? H-Heh, you're not being a silly goose, right?

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: <color=red>Error: I am not a goose.</color>

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: Ha. Ha. Ha.

Name: None
Dialogue: Before Main Duck's very eyes, whirring sounds buzz in the air as the Janitor cranes their neck and lets out a monotonous squawk.

Name: None
Dialogue: The janitor transforms into some mechanical monstrosity that has Main Duck's feathers standing on end. The janitor is a robot.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh, you gotta be quacking kidding with me...

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: <color=red>WARNING: CLEAN-UP CANNOT PERCEDE WITH INTEREFERING SUBJECT.</color>

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: <color=red>WARNING: ELON DUCK WOULD BE DISPLEASED.</color>

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: <color=red>INITIATE EMERGENCY PROCEDURE: KILL SUBJECT.</color>

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: HUH?!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh no, this is probably how Quackson died! I can't die here. Then I'll never see Duckette again!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I need to find a way to stop this robot Janitor!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I should try distracting the Janitor so I can make a run for it!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But what would distract the Janitor?

Name: None
Dialogue: LOOK! It's Elon Duck!

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: <color=red>CHANGE IN ORDERS: INITIATE PROPER GREETING FOR CREATOR.</color>

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Phew, I don't know how long that will distract the Janitor.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Ok, think Main Duck, think! I think now is my chance!

Name: None
Dialogue: You missed a spot over there!

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: <color=red>ERROR: MUST COMPLETE CLEAN-UP. CHECKING FOR SPOT INITIATED.</color>

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Phew, I don't know how long that will distract the Janitor.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Ok, think Main Duck, think! I think now is my chance!

Name: None
Dialogue: Did you hear something?

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: <color=red>ERROR: I DO NOT DETECT ANY ABNORMAL SOUNDS.</color>

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Phew, I don't know how long that will distract the Janitor.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Ok, think Main Duck, think! I think now is my chance!

Name: None
Dialogue: Please! Have mercy!

Name: Janitor
Dialogue: <color=red>ERROR: NO MERCY SHALL BE GRANTED TO SUBJECT WHO INTERFERES WITH CREATOR'S PLAN.</color>

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Phew, I don't know how long that will distract the Janitor.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Ok, think Main Duck, think! I think now is my chance!

Name: None
Dialogue: Main Duck notices something exposed from the Janitor's damaged head.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Huh, what's this over here?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh, these must be-

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: <color=red>Memory files!</color>

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I took one course in robotics, and these are super important for robots to function.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: These things record what the robot sees and does based on their assigned objectives by their creator.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: This is a quacking important piece of evidence! This should be enough to prove what the slaughterhouse is used for and the secret identity of the Janitor.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: T-That was quacking insane... I could've died!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But now with the Janitor out of the way, we should be safe for now.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But it's already late, and Donald would have come rushing in if he was still in the breakroom. He must've left already.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I guess I'll have to tell him what I found tomorrow.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: For now, I'll get the rest of the ducks and leave. There's no way I'm quacking staying here a minute longer!

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Thank you, sir, for meeting with me at such short notice.

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Of course, I'm happy to have the chance to meet with you Eggwin.

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: I believe in establishing one-on-one relationships with my employees, so if there are ever any problems, please feel free to reach out to me.

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: And from the email you sent me, it seems you have concerns with a fellow duck?

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Yes sir. I am worried about Main Duck.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I've only seen Main Duck in the morning today. And Donald, for whatever reason, took up their tasks for today instead of lounging in the breakroom.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I also noted that, while Main Duck did complete their tasks yesterday, they were running about and talking a lot with Donald. And we both know about Donald.

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Ah, yes. The delusional one.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Eggs-actly. I am worried that Main Duck is straying from their role in the team and is distracted by Donald's crazy theories.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: That is why, for the good of the company, I emailed you for a meeting to talk about Main Duck and hopefully get them back on the right track.

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Well, this is certainly quite a good reason for concern! I saw potential in our new employee, but it saddens me that they have been steered in the wrong direction!

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: However, I must commend you for your outstanding observation and dedication to the team! It is quacktastic to see how much you care for Nestla and the employees here.

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: I will think about the right course of action tonight and get back to you tomorrow. Do you mind if we meet tomorrow before the offices open to discuss more about Main Duck?

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Of course, sir! I understand it's already late, and I know you're a very busy duck.

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Hahaha, that's the life of a CEO.

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Well, you get on home now Eggwin. You are dismissed.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Thank you, sir. Goodnight.

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Goodnight.

Name: None
Dialogue: Once Eggwin leaves, Elon Duck checks the notification on his phone. He then frowns when he sees the janitor's location mysteriously disappearing on the map of Nestla.

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Looks like someone stuck their beak where they are not supposed to. Tomorrow will be a long day of cleaning up.

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: After all, no duck can know.

Scene: Find Donald to Discuss Findings in Killing Room
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: After escaping the slaughterhouse with all the ducks I saved, all of us immediately went home. I didn't have time to talk about what I found with Donald.

Scene: Find Donald to Discuss Findings in Killing Room
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I should find Donald. He needs to know about what I found out yesterday.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: There you are! I tried lingering behind after everyone left yesterday but I never saw you.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: And Eggwin wouldn't get out of my feathers if I didn't leave with everyone else. What did you-

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: DONALD! YOU WOULDN'T BELIEVE WHAT HAPPENED.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: First, the vents were like a maze! I almost got lost in there before I found an eggs-it.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: And then I thought that I was a free duck, but noooooo, my beak was practically to the floor with what I saw in that secret room.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: It's a slaughterhouse, Donald. Ducks were in cages; dead ducks were packed in boxes - I saw one of them being slaughtered by some cruel machine that we made.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: I knew it, that's where the missing ducks went.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: We're not making flying cars... we're making killing machines to kill off our own!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: It's almost like... a duck farm. Which matches that email we found in Elon Duck's Office! You found the operation behind Duckberry Farm here at Nestla!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But get this, I decided to be a quacking knight in shining feathers and save as many ducks as I could. I was practically risking my tailfeathers!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: And do you know the janitor?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: That duck who is always reminding everyone about the closing hours?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: WELL, THE JANITOR IS A ROBOT!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: I KNEW IT! No duck is that monotone.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: And the robot janitor tried to kill me! I could've been the next missing duck!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But I somehow managed to "deactivate" him and took out this memory card. I think this is the key to the secrets behind Nestla.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Great going Main Duck! I knew you would be the best partner for the job.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: This is the best evidence we could've gotten! We know where the missing ducks went, and we know what Nestla is hiding.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: We gotta tell the rest of the ducks about the evidence we found!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Yeah! We must stop Elon Duck and the Duckberry Farm! Only then can I find Duckette.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: *Whispers* Ok, all the ducks are here. They have no idea what we found!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: I need you to give the big speech, ok?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Me?! It's not like I raised my wing for this.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: And my feathers are still ruffled up from yesterday.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Come on, Main Duck! You have a better chance than me. Look at how well my speech went last time.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Ugh, he has a quacking point.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Come on, Main Duck. This is for Duckette and all of duck-kind. I got this!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: What are you waiting for?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: We have all the evidence we need. All that's left is convincing them with a big speech.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Everyone! Can I have your attention please?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I have come to report that we know what happened to the missing ducks. And I would like your help in avenging them!

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: *Sigh* Not another quacking speech.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But haven't you ever wondered what happened to the missing ducks?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Because I know. I've seen it with my own eyes.

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: Ok then. What happened to the missing ducks?

Name: None
Dialogue: They took a long vacation.

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: Are we supposed to quacking believe that?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oops, that wasn't the right explanation. Let me think about this again.

Name: None
Dialogue: They were sent to the slaughterhouse for the Duckberry Farm.

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: That sounds even more crazy that Donald's conspiracies!
