Name: Meggan
Dialogue: I mean, come on. A slaughterhouse? A duck farm?

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: Are you pulling our feathers or something? You think this is a funny joke?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: No, you gotta listen to me! We even have evidence to prove it.

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: Then prove it. What evidence do you have to prove that the slaughterhouse exists?

Name: None
Dialogue: They found a different job.

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: Are we supposed to quacking believe that?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oops, that wasn't the right explanation. Let me think about this again.

Name: None
Dialogue: They were duck-napped by robot ducks who plan to take over all of duck- kind.

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: Are we supposed to quacking believe that?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oops, that wasn't the right explanation. Let me think about this again.

Name: None
Dialogue: Show bloody feather.

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: And how does this "evidence" prove that the slaughterhouse exists?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Uh oh, wrong piece of evidence. Let me check my evidence again before presenting it.

Name: None
Dialogue: Show Duckette's necklace.

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: And how does this "evidence" prove that the slaughterhouse exists?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Uh oh, wrong piece of evidence. Let me check my evidence again before presenting it.

Name: None
Dialogue: Show your ruffled feathers as proof of the terror you witnessed.

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: And how does this "evidence" prove that the slaughterhouse exists?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Uh oh, wrong piece of evidence. Let me check my evidence again before presenting it.

Name: None
Dialogue: Show Janitor's memory files.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Right here are the <color=red>memory files</color> from the janitor that proves the slaughterhouse exists.

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: Memory files?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Yes, because the janitor is actually a robot that helps operate the slaughterhouse!

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: WHAAAAT?!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: If I play the memory files from here, you can see the janitor in the slaughterhouse. See all the cages lined with ducks?

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: Wait, some of those ducks do look familiar!

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: And what's that big machine over there? It looks familiar too.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: It's actually the killing machine. We're not making flying cars at all... we're making parts for this quacking killing machine!

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: NOOOOO!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: And these <color=red>memory files</color> duckument everything the janitor was doing in the slaughterhouse before I "deactivated" him.

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: Ok, but we must know one more thing about the janitor and the slaughterhouse.

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: How was the janitor getting to the slaughterhouse?

Name: None
Dialogue: The vents in the bathroom.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: The janitor used the vents in the bathroom. They're right above Quackson's stall.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: After all, that's how I was able to find the slaughterhouse.

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: Huh, that would be the perfect place. Barely any duck goes to the bathroom.

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: So, the janitor goes through the vents and helps operates the secret slaughterhouse, which is where the missing ducks went.

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: But what about the Duckberry Farm you mentioned earlier?

Name: Meggan
Dialogue: Who is responsible for the Duckberry Farm?

Name: None

Name: Main Duck

Name: Donald

Dialogue: LET IT BURNNNN!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Why am I surprised at this point...

Name: Donald

Name: Donald
Dialogue: ...Main Duck, are you even paying attention?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: No, why?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: You would think that he would have stopped us by now, or he would have lingered in the back to listen in.

Name: Main Duck

Name: Donald
Dialogue: I doubt he would join the Duck Union if that's your goal.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: So, your bomb is in this closet?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Yup, before the janitor took my keys, I used to hide all my findings and tools in here.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: But with the janitor gone, we'll need to use my lockpicking kit again.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Then hand it over. I got this. The sooner we find the bomb, the better.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Look at you! You're getting better and better at this lockpicking business.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Now, come on in! It's not every day you get a chance to see Donald's secret base.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Ta da! Welcome to my secret base! Well, one of my secret bases.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: It's... bigger than I thought.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Hopefully that janitor didn't get his feathers on any of my stuff.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: The bomb should be somewhere in here... but it's been a while.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Of course he forgot where the bomb is.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Welp, it's time to get searching.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hmm, let's check what's inside this box...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: E-Eggwin?

Name: None

Name: None
Dialogue: Horror is forever etched into his face as his glazed eyes stare beyond the ceiling.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Eggwin? EGGWIN!

Name: Donald

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: He's not waking up. He's dead. Just like Quackson, just like those ducks I found in the slaughterhouse.

Dialogue: Perhaps he was loyal to a fault... and it finally got to him.

Name: Donald

Name: Donald
Dialogue: ...Maybe Elon Duck found the Janitor and took the keys. He's probably already onto us.

Name: Donald

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Right. I don't want the next body I stumble upon to be Duckette's.

Name: Main Duck

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I think I found it!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But... is it supposed to look like this?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: No, it isn't. I bet that quacking janitor broke it.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: But it should be easy enough to put it back together again.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Think you got this?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Leave it to me!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: There, the bomb is properly assembled!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Quacktastic! I shall entrust you to keep the bomb safe for the big day tomorrow!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: I beak-lieve you know what to do with it.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Right. Blow the Duckberry Farm up and stop the fowl business once and for all.

Name: Donald

Name: Donald
Dialogue: We have obtained the bomb!

Name: Ducks
Dialogue: QUACK!

Name: Donald

Name: Ducks
Dialogue: QUACK!

Name: Main Duck

Name: Main Duck

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Today is finally the day...

Name: Donald
Dialogue: ...That we bring Elon Duck to justice!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Wow, every duck is here!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Of course, no duck would miss this for the world!

Name: Donald

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Ha, take that to every duck who called me crazy!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I still think Donald is a little on the cuckoo side. But for once, he was actually right about the missing ducks.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I just hope we can get answers about Duckette from Elon Duck during the confrontation.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Come on Main Duck, everyone is waiting for your cue.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I'm the leader?! Oh well...

Name: Main Duck

Name: Elon Duck

Scene: I found you Elon Duck... and Duckette?!

Dialogue: All this time, the humans have looked down on us, thinking they're the superior race compared to us.

Scene: I found you Elon Duck... and Duckette?!
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: We've evolved. Our intellect has the capacity to rival their own now.

Scene: I found you Elon Duck... and Duckette?!
Name: Elon Duck

Scene: I found you Elon Duck... and Duckette?!

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Now I'm simply killing ducks and sending them to the Duckberry Farm, but soon, I'll be in charge of the entire operation! Then the geese will truly be in equal standing with the humans.

Scene: I found you Elon Duck... and Duckette?!
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Alas! But I didn't account for my hesitation in my grand plan!

Scene: I found you Elon Duck... and Duckette?!
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hesitation? What hesitation? The slaughterhouse is still in full operation. I've seen enough dead bodies already this week to prove that.

Scene: I found you Elon Duck... and Duckette?!

Dialogue: But don't you see? Duckette is still right here. Isn't she one of your "missing ducks?"

Scene: I found you Elon Duck... and Duckette?!
Name: Main Duck

Scene: I found you Elon Duck... and Duckette?!
Name: Elon Duck

Scene: I found you Elon Duck... and Duckette?!
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: What a dilemma I was in! I am a goose, yet my heart has fallen for a duck. For Duckette.

Scene: I found you Elon Duck... and Duckette?!
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: So, she's my one eggs-ception. I let her accompany me in the office so long as she stays hidden. And she comes home with me so not a speck of blood stains her beautiful feathers.

Scene: I found you Elon Duck... and Duckette?!
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: You... If you so much as placed a quacking feather on Duckette I would-

Scene: I found you Elon Duck... and Duckette?!
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Would do what, Main Duck? Heh, I've already gotten what I wanted. I have the Duckberry Farm, I have my connection with the humans, and I have Duckette.

Scene: I found you Elon Duck... and Duckette?!
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: My plan is working perfectly, and this conversation is simply a waste of my time. I have other places I need to be. I'm a busy goose after all.

Scene: I found you Elon Duck... and Duckette?!
Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Goodbye little ducklings.

Scene: I found you Elon Duck... and Duckette?!
Name: None

Name: Donald
Dialogue: MAIN DUCK! ELON MANOR'S TRYING TO GET AWAY!

Name: Main Duck

Name: Donald

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Ducks
Dialogue: QUACK!

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: See Duckette? You're safe now!

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Hmm, it appears so.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Ok Main Duck, now is the perfect time to be the knight in shining feathers. Tell Duckette. Tell her now!

Name: Main Duck

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Iamsoquackinginlovewithyou.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Even now, you keep a brave face after everything Elon Manor has done to you.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: And you inspire me. You inspired me to be the hero I am today and save everyone, including you, from Elon Manor and the Duckberry Farm.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: So yeah, I'm in love with you.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: I know.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Wait, you knew?!

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: It was rather obvious, you and Elon Manor both.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: But I'm sorry. I'm already in love.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: ...WHAT.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: In love?! With who?

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: You wouldn't know him. His name is Manfred. Isn't that such a beak-tiful name?

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Manfred? Where have I seen that name before?

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Oh, the first time I met him on TweetHearts had me swimming in circles and joyfully kicking my webbed feet in the local pond.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: He's not a mate for one season, but a mate for life! His long, unruly beard that tickles my feathers, his toned arms that can easily lift two dozen ducks, his worn plaid shirt he always wears that's softer than any duck's feathers, his-

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Wait... from the sounds of him, he doesn't sound like a duck at all.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Oh, he's not a duck. Get this, he's a human! A farmer, no less. Great with other species, especially ducks.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Ah, we met right after graduation and have kept in touch ever since.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: I spent all my years at Purduck forever lonely and without a partner, searching for a love that was never there.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Who knew I was looking in the wrong flock?

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: That's why I wanted Elon Manor to kidnap me. My work requires me to email Elon Duck and the other partners of Nestla, so I knew from the codewords that there was some connection to the humans.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: So, I took a gamble, and I finally got to see him! After a year of only talking online and going on one or two dates, he's even better looking in the flesh!

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: And to think he's also one of the human partners for Nestla! We're truly meant to be.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: So, Elon Manor and the humans didn't hurt you?

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: The only thing I felt was my rapidly flapping heart.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: No, so that can't mean... I have to make sure.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: So, it's a... no?

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: It's a no. I already have Manfred, he's all I need.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: No! After all my hard work, a human took Duckette away from me?!

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I made sure to always talk to her in the office, we graduated together, I even saved everyone from Elon Duck and the Duckberry Farm!

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But the one person she falls in love with... is the same human who helped found the Duckberry Farm.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: How could she love someone like that?

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: It's... It's over. She doesn't love me. Not even a little bit.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Hehe, I'm sure Manfred will hear about what happened to Elon Duck and the Duckberry Farm.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Which means he'll come to visit! I better greet him outside.

Scene: Heartbroken and replaced by a human
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: ...Quacking Manfred. Just you wait.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Main Duck. I'm... I'm sorry about, well, you know...

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Look, you know what they say, that there are always more ducks in the flock, or something like that.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Besides, she's missing out! I mean, look at you, you just formed a Duck Union and saved everyone from the Duckberry Farm!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Well, Donald is right about one thing. Elon Manor and the Duckberry Farm is no more.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But what happens now? What do we do with all these ducks and this entire building?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Wait... I still have <color=red>Donald's bomb.</color> What if-

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Yes, it's perfect. Fire is always the best closure.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Everyone! To the lobby! We're leaving this place once and for all!

Name: Ducks
Dialogue: QUACK!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: You look like you have a plan. Lead the way.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: You look like you have a plan, so whatcha thinking up in that feathered brain of yours?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: ...I'm blowing this place up.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Wow, we have a new pyromaniac on our side now! Though I must say, I wouldn't miss this place in the slightest.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: And it'll be great to see my bomb in action.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: That makes the two of us.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Nestla. A place where I've experienced death, experienced heartbreak... yeah, there's only one thing left to do to a place like this.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: *Activates Timer on Bomb* Sayonara, Nestla.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: I thought it was the end of Nestla after that fateful day.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Elon Ducks body and that quacking Duck Farm burned in the night thanks to <color=red>my bomb.</color>

Name: Donald
Dialogue: So, Im sure youre thinking that the only thing left is some happily ever after to end a story like this.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Heh, if that was the case, why do you think Im hiding away in my bunker right now?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Anduck has risen over the fallen remains of Nestla, and many ducks have already flocked to work there only yesterday.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Ive heard strange things have been happening there too... worse than mere disappearances.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: And to think the CEO of the company is none other than Main Duck.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Maybe Elon Duck is to blame, maybe Duckette is to blame, maybe what Main Duck saw in the slaughterhouse that day is to blame.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: But Ive given up. No way am I working in a place like that ever again just to investigate another conspiracy.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Maybe I should retire. Or maybe I should try the entertainment industry. Many ducks quacked about that being the perfect place for a duck like me.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: I should warn you though, these ducks swim in circles in the same pond of greed. Join me, and swim as far away as you can before it's too late.

Name: None
Dialogue: The End?

Scene: Locked Room Dialogue - Elon Duck's Office
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: It's locked. Looks like Elon Duck isn't in the office today.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: It's locked. I wonder what the janitor hides in here.

Scene: Locked Room Dialogue - Killing Room (from vent)
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: It's locked. Then again, this is a vent. But why is it duck sized?

Scene: Locked Room Dialogue - Killing Room (from Manufacturing)
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: It's locked. I wonder what's behind it.

Scene: Locked Room Dialogue - Different Bathroom Stalls
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I really need to use the bathroom. Let me just go in this one- AHHHHHHH!

Scene: Locked Room Dialogue - Different Bathroom Stalls
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Traumatized for the rest of my duck years.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Looks like they're still running some simulation tests in there. It's best not to interrupt them.

Name: None

Name: None

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: You know Quackson-

Name: Quackson
Dialogue: Why are you here again? I'm kinda busy over here.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: On a scale of squawk to quack, what are the chances of me getting with Duckette?

Name: Quackson
Dialogue: ...There's an open stall next to mine with your name on it.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Never mind.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: You know, now that I think about it, does the boss know you're always in here?

Name: Quackson
Dialogue: What the boss doesn't know won't hurt him.

Name: Quackson
Dialogue: Besides, I'll have you know that I'm a producktive duck.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Says the one that doesn't even have an office desk to his name.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Quackson! Have you seen Duckette? She's gone missing!

Name: Quackson
Dialogue: Who?

Scene: Quackson Dialogue Day 4 - Before Finding Bloody Feather
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: You know, Duckette, the Fowl Temptress, the Beak-tiful Angel, the-

Scene: Quackson Dialogue Day 4 - Before Finding Bloody Feather
Name: Quackson
Dialogue: Does it look like I ever left this bathroom stall?

Scene: Quackson Dialogue Day 4 - Before Finding Bloody Feather
Name: Main Duck

Scene: Quackson Dialogue Day 4 - Before Finding Bloody Feather
Name: Quackson
Dialogue: Then I've never seen her.

Scene: Quackson Dialogue Day 5 - After Finding Body
Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: The bathroom stall is finally open... but at what cost?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hello! My name is Main Duck.

Name: Quackie
Dialogue: Oh, are you the new duck? That's so quacking cool!

Name: Quackie
Dialogue: You know, I was the new duck just last week!

Name: Quackie
Dialogue: I even joined Nestla with a few of my friends, but they quit within a few days.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh quack, is the work that hard?

Name: Quackie
Dialogue: Well, producktion for the new Model G has recently started, so it's definitely been busy.

Name: Quackie
Dialogue: I'm sure you'll have a good time here at Nestla though.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I better keep track of my tasks then!

Name: Billbert
Dialogue: ...I need another Energy Gooster.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Energy Gooster?

Name: Billbert
Dialogue: Oh my duck, have you never had an Energy Gooster in your life?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I've had the Red Roadrunner at Purduck University.

Name: Billbert
Dialogue: Nah, that one tastes like expired pond water mixed with rotting grapes.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Pond water expires?

Name: Billbert
Dialogue: Look, next time, if you need an ACTUAL drink, take a look at what's in our vending machine. There's quite the selection...

Name: Billbert
Dialogue: ...Including Energy Gooster.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Energy Gooster in the vending machine, noted. Maybe I should give it a try one day.

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: Hello! Are you my new neighbor?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Aww quack, I'm not next to Duckette!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: H-Heh, yeah! My name is Main Duck.

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: Nice to meet you! What do you specialize in?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh, well I studied Mechanical Engineering at Purduck University.

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: Purduck, huh?

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: I graduated from Induckana University.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I'm gonna return to work now.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I hope you have a quacktastic first day here at Nestla.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Thanks Eggwin!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Ah, I still can't believe I'm working alongside Duckette! What a dream come true!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: She's even more beak-tiful up close. At Purduck, she always sat at the other end of the classroom, and all the ducks would flock to the seats around her. I was stuck all the way in the back.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh if only my desk was next to hers though.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Um, can I help you?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: QUACK! I've been staring for too long! Act cool, act cool.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I lo-

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: *Cough* I lost my pen. Can I borrow one?

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: There should be a few extra pens at the receptionist's desk.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Worth a shot.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Don't get caught slacking.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Wow, what a pond-erful welcome.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hey! You're working on the producktion report with Duckette today, right?

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: Yes, why?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Do you want to... trade tasks with me?

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: No.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hey, I have a quacktion for you. You said you've been here for about a week, right?

Name: Quackie
Dialogue: Quack, you got it! What's up?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Well, I've been wondering if you know anything about Duckette, and how long she's been working here?

Name: Quackie
Dialogue: Oh, she's a recent hire too! She came in two days after me.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Wow... Duckette is new, yet she already fits the bill as a Nestla employee!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I gotta work hard to get to her level too.

Name: Billbert
Dialogue: Hey, are you grabbing a drink from the vending machine?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Yes, why?

Name: Billbert
Dialogue: Can you buy me an Energy Gooster too?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: What can are you even on?

Name: Billbert
Dialogue: 7. Which isn't enough. I haven't felt the caffeine waddle in yet.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I think that's plenty enough.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hey Duckette! If you ever need anything, just give me a quack!

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: ...Thanks intern.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh Duckette... when will you even remember my name?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I need to find a way to win her heart now that I have the chance.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Is Duckette still there?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I swear, if Donald even lays a wing on Duckette's feathers...

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Working hard today, Main Duck?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Quack, I am!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Working hard to win Duckette over.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Can you beak-lieve that Elon Duck is in the office today?

Name: Quackie
Dialogue: I know right? It's rare for Elon Duck to fly in.

Name: Quackie
Dialogue: Last time he came was last week to greet the newcomers and to tell us about hiring new recruits like you.

Name: Quackie
Dialogue: I hope I get a chance to talk to him today! He's such an inspiration for all of duck-kind.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hey, are you ok?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Huh, did they pass out or something?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: There are several empty Energy Gooster cans next to them. They probably just collapsed from all the caffeine.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I'll leave them be for now. They just gotta sleep it off.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Have you heard that-

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: Yes, I know. Elon Duck is here. His name is quacking out of everyone's beak today.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Are you not excited? It's Elon Duck!

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: Eh, I've already met him when he introduced me and a few others to Nestla. He's more of a celebrity than a CEO, popping up every now and then.

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: I wonder what is keeping him from coming to the office?

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Hm, so Elon Duck really is here. That means...

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Yes, I should send him an email. This is a great opportunity.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Opportunity?

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: *Sigh* Have you been peeping in this whole time?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Heh, sorry, I was planning to talk to you, but you seemed busy.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: I am busy. I have a few more emails I need to send out before the end of the day.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Make sure to finish your work in time too! After all, the CEO himself is here.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Quack, you're right! I should check to make sure I've finished everything for today.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: I'm on to you, Elon Duck.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh quack, not another one of Donald's conspiracies...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: You know, I can't help but ponder on how Donald hasn't been fired yet.

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Remember to leave no task unfinished Main Duck. We gotta do our best to impress Elon Duck!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Quack! You got it!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: One of my dreams, besides winning Duckette's heart, is to one day work for Elon Duck, and I'm finally living it!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: So I must show him how much of a producktive duck I am!

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Ah, you are-?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I'm Main Duck, sir! It's an honor to meet you!

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Ah, yes, Main Duck! You're one of our new employees, yes?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Yes, sir!

Name: Elon Duck
Dialogue: Then I look forward to seeing what you have to offer for Nestla's future.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hey, have you seen Duckette?

Name: Quackie
Dialogue: No, I haven't. But I don't think anyone will.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Why is that?

Name: Quackie
Dialogue: Because at the end of last week, I couldn't find my friend later. When I asked around, I learned that they quit.

Name: Quackie
Dialogue: Maybe your friend quit too and didn't want to tell anyone.

Name: Quackie
Dialogue: I only wish my friend told me.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hey, have you-

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: No, return to work.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I didn't even finish my quacktion.

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: Look, it's better to just continue working. Once you're here long enough, you'll get used to ducks leaving left and right.

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: Maybe Nestla is simply not for everyone.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: There's gotta be clues lying around here somewhere.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: Let me know if you find anything!

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Something on your mind, Main Duck?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Should I ask or...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: No, it's probably best to not ask now.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Nope! I'm just working hard as usual!

Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Good to hear! Give a quack if you need anything from me.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Huh, I've never seen this duck before. I wonder what happened to the other one?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Hey! Are you new?

Name: Quillson
Dialogue: Quack! I can't believe I'm actually inside Nestla's offices. It's been my quacking dream ever since I've learned to waddle.

Name: Quillson
Dialogue: By the way, my first task has something to do with CADs. Do you know where that is?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Oh, you should have a desk with your name tag on it. You can use the computer to complete your CAD assignment.

Name: Quillson
Dialogue: Ok, thanks for the help!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: No problem!

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Strange. Did the other duck simply leave or...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: ...Have they become the next missing duck in this case?

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: Hey, this time I have a quacktion for you.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: For me? What is it?

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: What do you think if I quit?

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Quit? As in quit your job?

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: Don't be a quackhead, of course that's what I meant.

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: But I don't know. Everyone's been acting strange lately. Even you.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Me?

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: You're rarely at your desk anymore, and you have a weird obsession with that Duckette girl.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: It's not weird, it's true love!

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: Yeah, right. I guess that's my answer.

Name: Duckelle
Dialogue: *Sigh* Maybe it's not too late to try my wing at making videogames than quacking cars.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: I can feel it! We're so close to discovering the truth!

Name: Donald
Dialogue: We just need that one piece of evidence that can stop all the retorts from flying out of each ducks' beak.

Scene: Eggwin Day 5 - Before Killing Room and Eggwin is a Snitch
Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: Remember our conversation, Main Duck.

Scene: Eggwin Day 5 - Before Killing Room and Eggwin is a Snitch
Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: We have a responsibility here at Nestla, both to Elon Duck and to all of birdkind.

Scene: Eggwin Day 5 - Before Killing Room and Eggwin is a Snitch
Name: Eggwin
Dialogue: I expect to see more great work from you today.

Name: Quillson
Dialogue: Huh, it's even emptier today.

Name: Quillson
Dialogue: Where did everyone go?

Name: Freggerico
Dialogue: I wonder what's going on. Every duck has flocked over here, even from the manufacturing room!

Name: Mal
Dialogue: Is Elon Duck coming? Is that why everyone's here?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: What are you waiting for?

Name: Donald
Dialogue: We have all the evidence we need. All that's left is convincing them with a big speech.

Name: Quillson
Dialogue: My feathers won't stop sticking up!

Name: Quillson
Dialogue: And to think I've always dreamed of working here... now I wish I never even applied for this job.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Same...

Name: Freggerico
Dialogue: Sorry. I... I need a second.

Name: Freggerico
Dialogue: M-My twin never came home yesterday. Does that mean they're already-

Name: None
Dialogue: I'm sure they're ok.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: Maybe they're somewhere else?

Name: Freggerico
Dialogue: Wherever they are... I hope they're safe.

Name: None
Dialogue: I'm sorry.

Name: Freggerico
Dialogue: ...Thank you.

Name: Freggerico
Dialogue: At least now, I can do something for them by joining the Duck Union.

Name: None
Dialogue: Tell them about saving the ducks.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I managed to save a few ducks when I was in the slaughterhouse.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: But many of the others were already dead.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: I think one of them looked like you. I'm not sure if they were your twin but...

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: They were already gone.

Name: Freggerico
Dialogue: Thanks for telling me the truth.

Name: Freggerico
Dialogue: Elon Duck... I'll make sure that fowl duck pays for what he's done to my family.

Name: None
Dialogue: Stay quiet.

Name: Freggerico
Dialogue: They're probably dead, right?

Name: Freggerico
Dialogue: The evidence is all there. There's no other eggs-planation.

Name: Freggerico
Dialogue: *Sob*

Name: Mal
Dialogue: Elon Duck... what a fowl villain!

Name: Mal
Dialogue: He's no longer a fellow duck in my eyes.

Name: Mal
Dialogue: Just you wait, I'm going to post the Duck Union and our victory against Elon Duck on SnapQuack. Then everyone will know Elon Duck's true feathers.

Scene: NPD 7 Day 7 - Before Finding Elon Duck
Name: Eggna
Dialogue: To think I'm part of the Duck Union and about to witness the downfall of Elon Duck.

Scene: NPD 7 Day 7 - Before Finding Elon Duck
Name: Eggna
Dialogue: I'm on the right side of history!

Scene: NPD 8 Day 7 - Before Finding Elon Duck
Name: Quacklyn
Dialogue: His office is unlocked! He should be in there!

Scene: Donald Day 7 - Before Finding Elon Duck
Name: Donald
Dialogue: There's no time to waste. Let's find that quacking Elon Duck and bring him and the Duckberry Farm down.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Hehe, I'm sure Manfred will hear about what happened to Elon Duck and the Duckberry Farm.

Name: Duckette
Dialogue: Which means he'll come to visit! I better greet him outside.

Name: Main Duck
Dialogue: ...Quacking Manfred. Just you wait.

Name: Donald
Dialogue: You look like you have a plan. Lead the way.
